Muhammad bin Abdullah-or son of Abdullah

94
00:07:08,962 --> 00:07:12,499
was born in the year 570
in the city of Mecca

95
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:15,202
in what is today Saudi Arabia.

96
00:07:18,472 --> 00:07:20,908
A poet of the times described Mecca

97
00:07:21,108 --> 00:07:25,546
as a place where winter and summer
were equally intolerable.

98
00:07:27,714 --> 00:07:31,718
The world into which Muhammad
arrived was a brutal one

99
00:07:32,119 --> 00:07:35,689
defined by hunger, violence,
and tribal warfare.

100
00:07:38,492 --> 00:07:41,161
You could not exist
without your tribe.

101
00:07:41,895 --> 00:07:46,500
An individual in this dangerous world
had absolutely no chance of survival.

102
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:51,572
And that meant that the tribe had become,
perhaps, the most sacred value in Arabia.

103
00:07:51,905 --> 00:07:56,777
It's a society that's based
on the idea of vigilantism.

104
00:07:57,177 --> 00:07:59,313
That, if somebody attacked my clan

105
00:07:59,646 --> 00:08:02,716
then I have a right to go and
attack anyone from his clan.

106
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:06,687
They saw justice as taking revenge.

107
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:11,825
The Arabs of the sixth century
had no written code of law

108
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:15,963
no common religion,
and no central government.

109
00:08:17,865 --> 00:08:19,666
In this dangerous world

110
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:25,305
Muhammad had the good fortune to be born
into Mecca's powerful tribe, the Quraysh.

111
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:31,945
But his father died before he was born,
and, his mother died when he was only 6.

112
00:08:32,946 --> 00:08:36,683
His uncle Abu Talib was left
to raise the young orphan.

113
00:08:37,951 --> 00:08:42,723
He surely had to have worried about
his future, what will he be.

114
00:08:43,423 --> 00:08:48,061
And so he he must have been
a very introspective child.

115
00:08:49,363 --> 00:08:53,867
Muhammad had the habit of going out
in the desert and contemplating

116
00:08:53,901 --> 00:08:57,070
the stars and thinking
about why he was an orphan.

117
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:59,573
And how would life be
to him in the future.

118
00:09:01,775 --> 00:09:04,578
Orphans were marginal people and

119
00:09:04,578 --> 00:09:07,814
he felt very,
very strongly identified

120
00:09:08,248 --> 00:09:11,585
with the poor and disadvantaged
for the rest of his life.

121
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:17,858
The Mecca of Muhammad's youth was both
a religious and a commercial center

122
00:09:18,225 --> 00:09:21,528
located at the crossroads
of two major trading routes.

123
00:09:23,997 --> 00:09:26,834
Pilgrims came from all
over Arabia to worship

124
00:09:26,934 --> 00:09:29,970
the hundreds of idols
that surrounded the Ka'aba

125
00:09:30,237 --> 00:09:32,573
an ancient shrine in
the heart of the city.

126
00:09:34,575 --> 00:09:39,279
The Ka'aba was surrounded by a sacred
area where fighting was not allowed.

127
00:09:41,215 --> 00:09:44,518
The commerce generated by
the pilgrims made it possible

128
00:09:44,518 --> 00:09:49,089
for a young man in Muhammad's circumstances
to make a living in the markets of Mecca.

129
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:55,229
Soon Muhammad began acting as
an agent for wealthy merchants

130
00:09:55,629 --> 00:09:58,632
taking their goods on caravans
throughout Arabia.

131
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,938
These journeys exposed him to a variety
of other tribes and communities

132
00:10:05,239 --> 00:10:07,174
and a range of new ideas.

133
00:10:08,775 --> 00:10:13,146
He probably learned the differences
that exist between different tribes.

134
00:10:13,847 --> 00:10:18,585
People speaking different languages.
He encountered Christians and Jews.

135
00:10:19,186 --> 00:10:22,122
And learned from them
what their faith

136
00:10:22,155 --> 00:10:25,225
what their religion,
what their cultures, are.

137
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:29,930
Muhammad would have become
aware that for the Jews

138
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:33,433
and the Christians the holy
scripture was very important.

139
00:10:34,535 --> 00:10:38,038
Both got scriptures
in which God had sent

140
00:10:38,305 --> 00:10:41,275
a sacred message to prophets

141
00:10:41,942 --> 00:10:46,246
and this was a way in which
people could relate to the divine.

142
00:10:49,049 --> 00:10:52,786
When MUHAMMAD was
about 25 years old

143
00:10:53,253 --> 00:10:55,455
he had a major change in his life.

144
00:10:55,822 --> 00:10:57,925
A wealthy widow

145
00:10:58,292 --> 00:10:59,993
older woman named KHADIJA

146
00:11:01,028 --> 00:11:05,065
asked him to take her caravans
into Syria for her.

147
00:11:06,533 --> 00:11:11,238
Muhammad took all her goods and
went with the caravan to Syria and did

148
00:11:11,705 --> 00:11:13,073
an incredible job.

149
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:18,745
And her respect for him turned
into admiration for him.

150
00:11:18,779 --> 00:11:21,281
And she inquired about him
through one of her friends.

151
00:11:23,884 --> 00:11:27,554
Shortly thereafter Khadija
asked Muhammad to marry her.

152
00:11:29,857 --> 00:11:32,526
I like you because of our
relationship, she said

153
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:35,329
"And your high reputation
among your people;"

154
00:11:36,330 --> 00:11:40,701
"Your trustworthiness,
good character, and truthfulness. "

155
00:11:42,069 --> 00:11:43,770
And this is interesting.

156
00:11:43,804 --> 00:11:45,205
She's is a very beautiful woman.

157
00:11:45,205 --> 00:11:46,406
But she's, she's 40.

158
00:11:46,406 --> 00:11:48,475
She is, she is moving into her maturity.

159
00:11:48,876 --> 00:11:50,777
And he's a 25-year-old youth.

160
00:11:51,144 --> 00:11:52,412
Um, he's an orphan.

161
00:11:52,746 --> 00:11:57,518
And, and he accepts this, uh, proposal
and it's arranged through the family.

162
00:11:57,551 --> 00:11:58,919
And he does, indeed, marry her.

163
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:01,822
And people have often said
rather sneeringly that

164
00:12:01,822 --> 00:12:04,525
this was just a marriage
of convenience on his part.

165
00:12:04,525 --> 00:12:08,929
He'd just married the wealthy widow
for his own ah gain and profit.

166
00:12:09,396 --> 00:12:13,834
But there's no doubt in my mind that
he deeply, deeply loved Khadija.

167
00:12:15,302 --> 00:12:19,773
Over the course of their marriage,
Khadija and Muhammad had four daughters

168
00:12:20,274 --> 00:12:22,376
and two sons who died as infants.

169
00:12:24,111 --> 00:12:27,714
He was a family man, and a successful
and respected merchant.

170
00:12:29,616 --> 00:12:32,586
But as Muhammad approached
his own fortieth birthday

171
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:35,789
he was becoming increasingly
restless and

172
00:12:35,789 --> 00:12:38,659
troubled by the problems
of Meccan society.

173
00:12:39,493 --> 00:12:40,894
Within a few generations

174
00:12:40,894 --> 00:12:46,166
they had gone from this kind of brutal
existence in the Arabian Steppes

175
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:49,536
to becoming financiers, bankers

176
00:12:49,736 --> 00:12:52,840
businessmen, merchants,
with a lot of money.

177
00:12:53,507 --> 00:12:57,678
And this was great, of course,
and people were delighted.

178
00:12:57,845 --> 00:13:01,181
But it was a very disturbing time

179
00:13:01,515 --> 00:13:04,751
because the market economy demanded

180
00:13:04,918 --> 00:13:09,056
as we know only too well in the West,
a strong competitive streak.

181
00:13:10,090 --> 00:13:14,061
People no longer felt that they had
to take care of the poor and the needy.

182
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:16,597
And the weaker members
of Quraysh any longer.

183
00:13:16,763 --> 00:13:19,166
They had to make as much money
at they possibly could.

184
00:13:20,634 --> 00:13:22,035
They had a marvelous society.

185
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:24,371
They had a trading town,
they were booming

186
00:13:24,371 --> 00:13:25,639
they were doing business.

187
00:13:25,806 --> 00:13:28,208
They were living like
an affluent society.

188
00:13:28,742 --> 00:13:31,044
And when you have
an affluent society

189
00:13:31,378 --> 00:13:33,413
the tendency is
to become hedonistic.

190
00:13:33,514 --> 00:13:35,883
To look at, you know,
what are the pleasures of life?

191
00:13:37,985 --> 00:13:43,023
Muhammad would often retreat
to the mountains outside Mecca, to meditate.

192
00:13:45,425 --> 00:13:50,864
It was on one such retreat in the
year 610 that Muhammad had an experience

193
00:13:51,131 --> 00:13:53,066
that would transform history.

194
00:13:54,401 --> 00:13:57,204
The prophet used to retire
from time to time

195
00:13:58,672 --> 00:14:01,742
into a hill called Jabal al-Nur,
the Mountain of Light.

196
00:14:07,481 --> 00:14:10,217
When you climb up that mountain and
many people still do it

197
00:14:11,251 --> 00:14:15,589
on top of it is a cave called
al-Hira in Arabic

198
00:14:16,723 --> 00:14:20,327
Into which the Prophet would often
times retire in order to contemplate

199
00:14:21,828 --> 00:14:22,663
and to pray.

200
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:24,298
To be still with God.

201
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:30,437
The coming of the revelation
was an immediate act.

202
00:14:33,473 --> 00:14:35,876
The descent from heaven
came suddenly.

203
00:14:38,645 --> 00:14:43,851
Muhammad was woken from sleep and
felt himself absolutely enveloped

204
00:14:43,851 --> 00:14:46,253
by a terrifying divine presence.

205
00:14:49,556 --> 00:14:52,826
He says it's an angel that
seemed to squeeze him

206
00:14:52,826 --> 00:14:55,395
ah, in a devastating embrace

207
00:14:55,696 --> 00:15:00,000
and it felt as though all the breath
was being squeezed out of his body.

208
00:15:01,235 --> 00:15:03,537
"And a voice said to him, "recite. "

209
00:15:06,306 --> 00:15:09,042
"And Muhammad said,
"no, I am not a reciter. "

210
00:15:09,042 --> 00:15:10,944
"The voice again said "recite"."

211
00:15:13,647 --> 00:15:14,615
Recite

212
00:15:17,851 --> 00:15:22,356
And then squeezed, as he said
almost beyond his endurance

213
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:28,495
Muhammad felt the first inspired words

214
00:15:28,495 --> 00:15:32,733
of a new scripture in Arabic
pouring from his lips.

215
00:15:36,970 --> 00:15:42,042
That is recite in the name
of thy lord who created.

216
00:15:44,244 --> 00:15:46,780
And Islam had come into being.

217
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:52,920
And the prophet of course having
received the divine word

218
00:15:53,921 --> 00:15:57,124
began to tremble and tremendous fear

219
00:15:58,025 --> 00:16:01,828
because there's no common groundbetween
the human reality and the divine reality

220
00:16:02,062 --> 00:16:03,163
When he ran out of the cave

221
