1390
01:36:20,581 --> 01:36:23,884
And he went out and
he sacrificed one of the camels

1391
01:36:23,884 --> 01:36:27,488
and somehow some kind of necessary
tension was released.

1392
01:36:31,592 --> 01:36:36,530
The ritual sacrifice of an animal
traditionally marked the end of the pilgrimage.

1393
01:36:37,264 --> 01:36:40,968
Grudgingly, the Muslims considered
the pilgrimage complete

1394
01:36:41,101 --> 01:36:42,669
and headed back to Medina.

1395
01:36:43,437 --> 01:36:47,641
Muhammad had compromised on every
major point in the treaty.

1396
01:36:47,941 --> 01:36:51,044
But he had won the most
significant concession.

1397
01:36:51,645 --> 01:36:55,249
In return for postponing their
entry into Mecca for a year

1398
01:36:55,849 --> 01:36:58,852
the Muslims had secured
ten years of peace

1399
01:36:59,119 --> 01:37:02,189
and official recognition
as a political entity.

1400
01:37:02,856 --> 01:37:07,995
Muhammad had proved himself as capable
a diplomat as he was a religious leader.

1401
01:37:10,664 --> 01:37:12,699
There was wisdom in the treaty

1402
01:37:13,200 --> 01:37:15,869
because one of the things that
was promised to the Muslims

1403
01:37:16,870 --> 01:37:20,073
was protection as they moved
throughout Arabia.

1404
01:37:20,374 --> 01:37:22,242
That they would not be harmed and
they could move freely.

1405
01:37:23,677 --> 01:37:29,249
And what was gained most greatly from that
was the dauwa, the teaching of al-Islam.

1406
01:37:30,818 --> 01:37:35,322
On the way back to Medina,
Muhammad told a companion, Umar

1407
01:37:35,322 --> 01:37:40,561
I have received a revelation which is dearer
to me than anything else beneath the sun.

1408
01:37:41,195 --> 01:37:45,599
it said, "Surely",
"We have given you a clear victory. "

1409
01:37:47,067 --> 01:37:50,737
Then more and more and more
people came to Islam

1410
01:37:50,771 --> 01:37:52,673
more and more people turned to MUHAMMAD.

1411
01:37:52,673 --> 01:37:55,475
It sent out a huge signal of strength.

1412
01:37:55,475 --> 01:38:02,115
Strength of purpose, utter courage, utter
panache, and utter wisdom that, of course

1413
01:38:02,115 --> 01:38:03,150
you could go on to fight

1414
01:38:03,250 --> 01:38:06,587
of course he could have gone on being
the prophet with the sword

1415
01:38:06,653 --> 01:38:10,958
but there are times when
to make peace is more daring

1416
01:38:11,158 --> 01:38:13,327
more creative, and more enduring.

1417
01:38:16,730 --> 01:38:20,000
One year after signing
the Hudaybiyah treaty,

1418
01:38:20,200 --> 01:38:23,971
Muhammad led his followers on
a new pilgrimage to Mecca.

1419
01:38:25,239 --> 01:38:29,476
After years of rejection,
persecution, and humiliation

1420
01:38:29,877 --> 01:38:32,946
this was truly a moment of triumph.

1421
01:38:34,681 --> 01:38:38,152
The first pilgrimage of the Muslims

1422
01:38:38,152 --> 01:38:43,357
after Hudaybiyah must have been
an extraordinary event for everybody.

1423
01:38:43,824 --> 01:38:45,692
Because the MECCANS couldn't bear it.

1424
01:38:46,193 --> 01:38:50,998
They decamped and went and sat up in
the hills and mountains outside the city, and

1425
01:38:50,998 --> 01:38:57,371
watched this procession, huge procession
of Muslims, and some of their confederates

1426
01:38:57,538 --> 01:39:02,142
coming on the HAJJ, and as it were,
taking possession of the city

1427
01:39:02,142 --> 01:39:07,314
crying out the pilgrim cry, here I am, oh,
God, here I come, in a huge cry.

1428
01:39:07,981 --> 01:39:12,319
Then came the moment Muhammad had waited
seven long years to achieve.

1429
01:39:12,953 --> 01:39:15,722
Muhammad sends Bilal, an African ex-slave

1430
01:39:16,223 --> 01:39:18,895
this lowest of the low
in the eyes of the Meccans

1431
01:39:18,900 --> 01:39:21,895
up on to the sacred shrine of the Ka'aba

1432
01:39:22,996 --> 01:39:25,599
what the Meccans regard as their shrine

1433
01:39:27,301 --> 01:39:28,936
to deliver the call to prayer.

1434
01:39:30,404 --> 01:39:32,673
And the hills around Mecca are granite.

1435
01:39:32,873 --> 01:39:35,242
They're set up for a sonorous voice.

1436
01:39:35,976 --> 01:39:39,713
And the call to prayer resonates
through the valley.

1437
01:40:28,395 --> 01:40:35,502
Bilal was proclaiming for all to hear,
there is one God and Muhammad is his Prophet.

1438
01:40:37,704 --> 01:40:41,542
It must have been an appalling moment
for the MECCANS.

1439
01:40:41,842 --> 01:40:45,879
But an extraordinary moment
of exhilaration for the Muslims.

1440
01:40:46,213 --> 01:40:48,649
Performing all the rites punctiliously

1441
01:40:48,782 --> 01:40:53,687
and then taking no advantage of this,
going back peacefully home.

1442
01:40:58,058 --> 01:41:01,929
But the peace between the Muslims and
the people of Mecca would not last.

1443
01:41:02,262 --> 01:41:06,133
By the end of the year, the Meccans
had broken the Treaty of Hudaybiyah

1444
01:41:06,400 --> 01:41:09,469
by attacking a clan allied with Muhammad.

1445
01:41:10,003 --> 01:41:13,774
In response, 10 days into
the holy month of Ramadan

1446
01:41:14,041 --> 01:41:20,013
Muhammad and a Muslim army of 10,000 men
set out to take Mecca by force.

1447
01:41:21,248 --> 01:41:24,985
The Prophet felt he was strong enough
to be able to conquer MECCA.

1448
01:41:26,653 --> 01:41:31,725
But as the army approached the city,
more and more leaders of the Quraysh

1449
01:41:32,092 --> 01:41:38,499
realized that they were not going to win,
and so many decided to join Islam.

1450
01:41:41,502 --> 01:41:44,571
The prophet entered the city
without resistance.

1451
01:41:45,239 --> 01:41:48,041
When he came into Mecca he came
in with his head bowed down.

1452
01:41:48,175 --> 01:41:52,880
He did not come in as, as,
as an arrogant conquering warrior.

1453
01:41:52,980 --> 01:41:57,351
He comes in humbled by a victory
that he sees is from God.

1454
01:41:58,452 --> 01:42:01,054
After circling the Ka'aba seven times

1455
01:42:01,255 --> 01:42:05,626
Muhammad destroyed each of the three
hundred sixty idols that surrounded it.

1456
01:42:06,160 --> 01:42:10,597
He then turned to the vanquished Meccans
who had sought refuge inside the shrine.

1457
01:42:10,998 --> 01:42:15,769
His own brethren, who had oppressed and
attacked the Muslims for so many years.

1458
01:42:17,204 --> 01:42:22,776
He says, if you were in my position right now,
what do you think you would do

1459
01:42:24,278 --> 01:42:28,649
and the Meccans are afraid
they're about to die.

1460
01:42:29,750 --> 01:42:33,320
And then he says, you are all pardoned.

1461
01:42:34,188 --> 01:42:35,923
He grants them all amnesty.

1462
01:42:36,890 --> 01:42:41,528
And this was unheard of in this culture,
unheard of in this society.

1463
01:42:41,895 --> 01:42:44,598
And very unexpected among the Meccans.

1464
01:42:51,839 --> 01:42:55,676
The religion that had begun
in ridicule and persecution

1465
01:42:55,943 --> 01:42:59,279
was now thriving throughout
the Arabian peninsula.

1466
01:43:00,781 --> 01:43:06,453
But shortly after returning to Medina,
Muhammad received a premonition of his death.

1467
01:43:08,889 --> 01:43:12,960
He told his daughter Fatima that
every year during Ramadan

1468
01:43:13,160 --> 01:43:17,831
the angel Gabriel recited the Quran
to him and asked him to repeat it.

1469
01:43:18,298 --> 01:43:22,803
This year Gabriel had asked Muhammad
to recite the Quran twice.

1470
01:43:23,871 --> 01:43:28,909
I cannot but think, Muhammad said,
that my time has come.

1471
01:43:32,379 --> 01:43:34,515
In February 632

1472
01:43:34,882 --> 01:43:39,820
Muhammad made what would be his final
pilgrimage to the city of his birth.

1473
01:43:40,621 --> 01:43:45,058
On his first pilgrimage, he had led
a few hundred Muslims back to Mecca.

1474
01:43:45,592 --> 01:43:50,998
This time, tens of thousands of believers
followed in his footsteps.

1475
01:43:53,767 --> 01:43:55,235
He arrives in Mecca

1476
01:43:56,470 --> 01:44:01,341
as the leader of the Muslim people now,
not as the enemy of the Meccans.

1477
01:44:01,942 --> 01:44:06,079
And they begin to perform
the rites of the pilgrimage.

1478
01:44:06,814 --> 01:44:08,148
And during this period

1479
01:44:08,582 --> 01:44:14,354
Muhammad defines the rites of pilgrimage as
they're performed today.

1480
01:44:17,090 --> 01:44:21,128
Michael Wolfe has written
extensively about the Hajj

1481
01:44:21,328 --> 01:44:26,934
the traditional pilgrimage which every Muslim
is expected to perform at least once.

1482
01:44:27,701 --> 01:44:32,206
Two to three million Muslims from
around the world travel to Mecca

1483
01:44:32,206 --> 01:44:37,611
every year for this five day ritual,
which takes them in the footsteps of Abraham

1484
01:44:38,011 --> 01:44:44,218
the ancient patriarch from whom Muslims,
Jews, and Christians all trace their lineage.

1485
01:44:45,419 --> 01:44:51,225
In 1990 Michael Wolfe, a convert to Islam,
took part in his first Hajj.

1486
01:44:56,630 --> 01:45:00,000
The Hajj was one of the most
attractive elements

1487
01:45:00,734 --> 01:45:08,575
in Islam to me as a non-Muslim and
then as a Muslim.

1488
01:45:09,376 --> 01:45:13,881
When I finally became a Muslim
after 20 or more years of thinking it over

1489
01:45:14,815 --> 01:45:17,518
the first thing I wanted to do was
make the Hajj.

1490
01:45:21,788 --> 01:45:26,193
When I circled the Ka'aba for the first time,
I was in a state of wonder.

1491
01:45:26,727 --> 01:45:31,498
You're there with ten of thousands of people,
all doing the same thing at once.

1492
01:45:34,101 --> 01:45:37,204
You're literally putting
God at the center of your life.

1493
01:45:37,738 --> 01:45:39,840
For that period of time.

1494
01:45:52,619 --> 01:45:55,956
At the culmination of the Hajj,
on the Plain of Arafat

1495
01:45:56,089 --> 01:46:01,495
on a small hill called the Mount of Mercy,
Muhammad gave his final sermon.

1496
01:46:02,963 --> 01:46:10,003
Here is a man who began his mission
as this individual in Mecca, persecuted, with

1497
01:46:10,003 --> 01:46:15,509
with almost no followers, and his life
is completed with a valley filled

1498
01:46:15,509 --> 01:46:20,414
with tens of thousands of people, uh,
that have accepted his message.

1499
01:46:20,814 --> 01:46:24,618
And, and there he is,
preaching to them his final sermon.

1500
01:46:24,751 --> 01:46:29,723
And in it in a sense is a summation
of this universal teaching.

1501
01:46:30,224 --> 01:46:35,762
He tells them to be good to each other,
and not to violate each other's rights.

1502
01:46:36,163 --> 01:46:41,268
For men and women to treat each other
humanely, for brothers and sisters to treat

1503
01:46:41,268 --> 01:46:45,172
each other well, and for Muslims to treat
each other as brothers and sisters.

1504
01:46:46,039 --> 01:46:52,312
And perhaps most importantly,
he calls an end to revenge, to blood killing

1505
01:46:52,813 --> 01:46:54,114
to the vendetta

1506
01:46:54,882 --> 01:47:00,254
which has bled this culture terribly
since he was born.

1507
01:47:00,954 --> 01:47:07,528
At the end of Muhammad's sermon,
he does not list his achievements.

1508
01:47:07,961 --> 01:47:10,998
This man has unified people.

1509
01:47:11,532 --> 01:47:14,501
He has taught them monotheism.

1510
01:47:15,502 --> 01:47:18,772
He has brought them to peace.

1511
01:47:18,906 --> 01:47:22,843
And yet he doesn't mark these
as his accomplishments.

1512
01:47:23,243 --> 01:47:26,113
Quite the opposite,
he asks his community

1513
01:47:26,446 --> 01:47:30,684
"Have I fulfilled my mission"

1514
01:47:31,318 --> 01:47:34,154
"To my God, and to you?"

1515
01:47:34,788 --> 01:47:41,328
You can hear in his words the desire
for a completed mission.

1516
01:47:42,229 --> 01:47:47,935
This is a man of faith
who is unsure of his affects.

1517
01:47:48,335 --> 01:47:54,474
It's a very human moment in which
he needs to know, and he asks

1518
01:47:55,609 --> 01:47:59,613
and the people affirm that yes,
three times they say, yes

1519
01:48:00,247 --> 01:48:01,849
you have fulfilled your mission.

1520
01:48:05,018 --> 01:48:10,457
This, was not a leader who was looking
for his legacy in time.

1521
01:48:10,757 --> 01:48:15,562
It wasn't for any purpose other than
to make sure that

1522
01:48:15,629 --> 01:48:19,500
when he was going to face his maker,
he was going to be accountable.

1523
01:48:20,100 --> 01:48:24,872
And he was, he would be in a position
of saying Allah, I did the best I could.

1524
01:48:24,872 --> 01:48:27,841
And, and I hope I was
successful in doing it.

1525
01:48:28,775 --> 01:48:32,179
Uh, and that's all what
we can do as human beings.

1526
01:48:37,518 --> 01:48:42,422
I think that if I were to say that
I hope to exemplify

1527
01:48:42,523 --> 01:48:44,725
any part of Prophet Muhammad's life

1528
01:48:45,092 --> 01:48:49,129
it would be the issues around
the dignity near the end of life.

1529
01:48:51,565 --> 01:48:56,003
He's a good friend of mine and
I know he knows my voice.

1530
01:48:56,036 --> 01:48:58,038
And now I know for sure
he knows my voice.

1531
01:49:01,108 --> 01:49:07,181
I'm visiting Mr. Hamoud,
who is a patient that's terminal.

1532
01:49:12,653 --> 01:49:17,291
When he was not in the condition
he's in now, he was very delightful

1533
01:49:17,291 --> 01:49:22,062
very loving and very much wanting
to tell his story

1534
01:49:22,062 --> 01:49:24,965
so we'd sit and listen and talk
for long hours and

1535
01:49:24,965 --> 01:49:28,635
he'd give me all his history and his past,
so we're very bonded.

1536
01:49:31,638 --> 01:49:35,309
Um, he's slipped into a more terminal stage,
meaning less responsive.

1537
01:49:35,609 --> 01:49:37,511
Well he responds,
he's just unable to speak.

1538
01:49:40,747 --> 01:49:44,818
Prophet Muhammad has taught us that
near the time of death, the holy Quran

1539
01:49:44,985 --> 01:49:47,554
to hear is soothing,
very soothing to the soul.

1540
01:49:48,455 --> 01:49:52,559
And since it's a part of our lives
on a daily basis anyway

1541
01:49:52,559 --> 01:49:55,896
we derive great comfort from
the hearing of the Quran.

1542
01:49:57,564 --> 01:50:01,335
While I'm stroking a head or
I'm speaking softly

1543
01:50:01,969 --> 01:50:04,304
I say the things that
I think Muhammad would say.

1544
01:50:05,539 --> 01:50:06,373
Prophet

1545
01:50:06,607 --> 01:50:08,342
Muhammad has taught us that

1546
01:50:08,575 --> 01:50:11,011
we don't even understand,
we could never comprehend

1547
01:50:11,011 --> 01:50:15,182
the value of taking care of the ill or
providing for the dying

1548
01:50:15,516 --> 01:50:17,284
maintaining their dignity.

1549
01:50:18,652 --> 01:50:22,489
And I believe that that's my mission,
to be the helper, to be the listener

1550
01:50:23,490 --> 01:50:25,792
to be a comforter in many ways.

1551
01:50:34,468 --> 01:50:37,738
The Prophet knew that death was coming

1552
01:50:37,971 --> 01:50:41,575
he had an indication that he would not be
around for much longer.

